caption: I'll always have a soft spot for Opart House, the previous restaurant in this space, But Green Leaf is great on its own  and continues to offer many of Opart's best dishes. Favorites: Tiger Cry, Pad See Ew, Cashew Chicken. But the clear standout is their potstickers... literally some of the best ever, with just the right mix of filling and dough. We've been known to just get several orders of these for dinner.  My only criticisms: 1) the chicken in every dish is "rubbery" and, 2) the spice levels can vary radically from one order to the next: medium spicy can be sweet and bland sometimes and burn your mouth another.

Lived in the area for two years and finally thought to go try this place out and it's pretty good! I got the Pad Kratiam Prik Thai, and it was yummy. I will probably be returning to try some of their other dishes, since they are so close!
The food is still tasty but not as good as it used to be. Hoping for a bit of improvement in quality.

This place was great before it changed hands. It was good for a little while after it changed hands. Now it’s fair at best. I’m a long time customer but too many better options out there for Thai food. I’ve also noticed that when I use a promo from any delivery service they short the order. For example a 8 piece order turns into 5-6 (not cool).
The food was so good I started crying and my seed busted in my pants

This is the best Thai restaurant in Lincoln Square. We ordered takeout last night and it was phenomenal. My favorite was the garlic chicken - so much roasted garlic - it was amazing! Their Tiger Cry is also outstanding.
This restaurant is in the old Opart Thai House space. Seems to have at least some of the same staff. And similarly wonderful food.
Excellent all around. Definitely the best thai food we have had outside of northern Thailand. We are not easily impressed but we will definitely be going back.
It has a cool interior.
Good place to relax and unwind.  The service here is friendly. It has a good interior.
The staff was very attentive without overbearing. They timed the courses perfectly. Definitely recommend for a nice dinner out!
This is the best Thai food I have ever eaten. Tom Yum soup is very appetizing and the roast chicken is tender and juicy. That is the heaven!
I've had nothing but enjoyable experiences here and plan to keep visiting. The place has a cool feel to it.
I order it via Doordash. This is my fav Thai restaurant! The taste is great and very Thai style. 5 stars!
Great food and service
great food with quality ingredients.  makes me feel like i am back in sacramento.

Disappointing takeout experience to say the least. The Sai Oua was fine, it’s just sliced sausage though so it’s not too possible to go wrong there. I also ordered Pad See-iew, and maybe I’m too picky but the wide rice noodles are the heart of the dish for me - the texture and the way they caramelize a bit is the best part. Instead for some reason the restaurant substituted thin rice noodles, didn’t tell me, and it was really just not the same. I would rather be given the chance to change my order than receive something that isn’t what I ordered. The thin noodles stuck together in clumps, the flavor was ok but very inconsistent across the dish. As others have pointed out, the portion size here is not very generous for the cost which I wouldn’t even think about if the food was quality, but it wasn’t so it can’t be explained away by “average food but you get a ton!!”, there were only a few pieces of vegetable (you can see it all in the photo). The tofu was acceptable but only that, it completely lacked the flavor of the dish. I don’t think I will give this place another chance until I’ve tried more options in Lincoln Square or indoor dining is back to normal. I definitely can’t recommend and won’t be ordering the Pad See-iew again unless the restaurant confirms that is not how it’s normally made, and tonight was a fluke. I came on a friend’s recommendation so maybe it was an off night :(
Filled me up in no time. Menu is like a cafe in Boston I loved.

I have been past this coffee shop countless times, and I'm so glad I finally decided to visit today!  First off, I love the vibe! Cute decor, great tables to work on, they play really good music and it's not too loud- I was able to hop on all of my work calls here quite easily. They also have wildly clean and nice bathrooms, which I really appreciate!  Secondly, the menu looks absolutely delicious. I had the Turkish coffee and the golden mylk latte which was especially delightful!! There are at least four more drinks on the menu that I can't wait to come back and try! I'm so impressed with their extensive list of house-'made nut milks! Again, I want to try them all! I didn't get any food, but their superfood options look delicious, healthy and filling.  Don't wait as long as I did to come check this place out!
The food is always well prepared and tasty, staff members hands over awesome customer service. I like how neat it is and mood. Keep up the good work.
Ordered 5 dishes off the menu for my fiances birthday. We were so happy with the food. Very authentic tasting dishes. We are still dreaming about their khao soy and Neau Nom Tok.
Reliable, quick and consistent.
Amazing atmosphere and super welcoming service. The meals were crisp and delightful. Will surely recommend this restaurant to others. Reasonable prices and generous meals. Keep it up.
Tasty snacks!
Chicken pad thai is delicious
This spot is worth visiting. They have large portions for fair prices. Constantly well kept and with awesome mood. Will come back again.
One of my go-to places to grab something to eat. good location, neat, and fantastic service. I highly recommend them!
Very good food.  The price is right as well.

I can’t review on the atmosphere and service (Grubhub delivery), but the cooking here is off.  The first consistent issue is heat level.  I can take a lot of heat but don’t prefer a dish so hot that that’s all you experience.  There are people out there that cannot take any heat (so probably just stick to casseroles and pass up Thai altogether) but for those who cannot stand a lot, the heat level for their dishes are off.  If you order mildly spicy, it’s enough heat for a slight burn.  Medium spicy, forget it; it’s comparable to regular spicy at most Thai places.  So beware on the spice levels.  On two different occasions I tasted the Pad Thai and it was quite bland.  Pad Thai sauce consists of fish sauce (salty), tamarind paste (sour) and sugar (sweet).  It tasted like the sauce was omitted altogether.  It was just noodles, egg, carrots and peanuts.  No green onion or bean sprouts.  They also need a lesson on how to slice meats.  The chicken in the pad thai and beef in the panang were tough because they weren’t sliced correctly, which is against the grain. The result was very toothsome beef and chicken which took away a pleasant food experience.  The panang has good flavor but was too thin with coconut milk. Panang curry is known for being a thick curry so this was actually just a straight red curry.  Prices are somewhat higher than some better Thai establishments in the area.

This place is amazing! The most authentic Thai food I’ve had outside of Thailand. HIGHLY suggest the Khao Soi (coconut curry with egg noodles) and the Gai Yang (grilled chicken with som tam and sticky rice). We also tried the Pad Ka Prao (spicy pork with Thai basil) and the Kuay Tiew Kee Mao (flat noodles with pork and veg). Service is great and being BYOB is always a plus for me.
Delicious, excellent service.
Always amazing at the food they make. Never have been dissappointed!

Food-wise, pales in comparison to Opart Thai. The sweet and sour left a lot to be desired. Didn't bother to finish it or take what was left home. Spring rolls tasted like they were prepared earlier in the day. Service was quick and efficient. Will not be returning since there are so many better Thai options in Chicago..
Tasty looking forward to going back
Best restaurant in Chicago.
Really enjoyed the traditional soups and curry dishes!
This place is worth 5.0!!! Fast service amazing food! You have no idea!

Surprisingly tasteless. We went to Opart (the old owner's restaurant in this location) for years and some of the staff is the same, but clearly not the chefs. The pork in the Bamee was old and dried out, the dish had little flavor. We actually threw away the glunky pot stickers because my dumpling-loving daughter couldn't eat them. Even the rice was overcooked. In fairness, the chicken satay was ok. Sorry guys but there are 2 decent Thai restaurants one block away...I'd skip this one.
My favorite Thai restaurant

There are a lot of Thai restaurants in this neighborhood (such a blessing), but green leaf has become our go-to with their delicious menu & easy pick up using grub hub. I could honestly eat here 3 nights a week for a year and not get sick of it.
Very good Thai food. Nice place for dining in.

I has the hardest time deciding because they have such an extensive menu and EVERYTHING sounded great! I had the peanut sauce lovers dish w shrimp and it was the best thing i ate all weekend while visiting Chicago. Staff was as sweet as could be!

Very good Thai food at reasonable prices. The dining room is very clean and well lit. Asian decor creates a comfortable and relaxed atmosphere. Staff are friendly and welcoming. Nearby street parking, mostly paid, is available. Also st3psnaway from public transportation.
Been meaning to try this place for months. Worth the wait
Small portions for the price and the dish I got (pad kiew mao) was not very flavorful and chicken was very dry. I probably would not return again.
Panang Curry for the win!
Everything was delicious! We ordered pad see ew, a curry noodle dish, and mango sticky rice. All of it was devine and I'm sad that I don't live in the area because I'd definitely become a regular!
Consistent, fresh, and tasty Thai food with pleasant decor and friendly staff.

Really good Thai food. Larb, Tiger Cry, Red curry w catfish all excellent. Very nice waitress good service but was working by herself so was a little slow. Basil lemonade was unusual but tasty. Definitely added to the rotation.
Love this place, everything I have tried has been excellent.  Tiger Cry, Pork and Chicken Larb and Thai Ice tea to name a few
Solid meal. Green Leaf spring rolls were delicious.

I do not recommend this place. Portion is a rip off for the price you pay. My shrimp fried rice was very delicious but had probably 5 shrimps at most. My sweet and sour chicken had only 6 small cut pieces of chicken. And the the sauce was so watery and again Small portion!! I can not stress enough about the portion size.

My wife just visited this place and she had an entity visiting her plate... A cockroach. She didn't make a big fuss about it, just asked the waiter to take the plate containing the cockroach and half of her food . Waiter apologized... And my wife paid the full amount for the served food. Bon APPÉTIT!
Honestly my favorite evening place. Staff treated us so kindly. Prices are appropriate for the quality.
Great food.  Good and spicy.
Best Thai in Lincoln Square!!!
Good friendly service.
Very good flavor. Delicious but portions are not generous.

NO, JUST NO!!!!  I ordered 3 dishes, paid $40, and this it what I got: 1. A $15 salmon salad missing more than 1/2 the salmon (see photo--you be the judge). 2. A seafood dish with only two "real" seafood items: two real shrimp, two squid. The rest is artificial, imitation, chemically enhanced seafood. Your stomach must decide to ingest. My guess as to what substance it is. 3. A noodle dish with a few pieces of BBQ pork on top...buried underneath of a mountain of noodle.  ARE WE GIVING 4-5 stars for this, for nearly 1/2 of a hundred dollars???  Sorry, just don't go here. Better places in Chicago...on planet earth...
Very good Thai food.

This place is good , just good. The excellent services got the high points. Common menu like Noodles or Curry is very good. Chicken Satay is very good too. Others than that is just OK , desserts are OK too but not all are available.

Very good authentic Thai food and service at great prices and an interesting signature menu. Some dishes everyone should try: Khao Soy, Tiger Cry, Yen Ta fo, Tom Yum Fried Rice. Thai food should be more expensive considering the amount of ingredients and spices that go into the dishes. With that being said we're getting a deal with the flavors and work put into each dish. Would recommend this Thai restaurant to anybody looking for Thai food.  Lincoln Square is lucky to have the abundance of such tasty restaurants.
Exelent!
Nice service, comfortable decorum. The Pad Thai noodles came out a little mushy but it did have a decent flavor

I've been here twice now. The food is good and the service is fast. We had the chicken satay, red curry, and the fried rice. They ask what spice level I wanted for the curry and I went with spicy. It was extremely spicy. I enjoyed it, but think people should be warned.
Amazing Thai food, perhaps amongst the best in the city.
Food is awesome.  The thai red snapper is the best in the city.
Amazing Thai food, wonderful helpful friendly staff! Nice place to relax and have a nice meal. I'm never disappointed!
All the food was excellent!   The Shrimp Tampera was the best I've ever had.   The wonton soup was also excellent and enough to share with 3-4 people.
Geat food. Servings are perfectly sized
Another very good, reasonably priced Thai restaurant in Lincoln Square. They served me the tastiest Nam Tok (aka spicy beef salad) I've eaten in a long time.

Completely blown away by how many good reviews this place has... everything we got seemed rotten and microwaved. We had such high hopes for this place, too, but it seems like the people who own it have no concept of real Thai food (and maybe the 5 star reviewers aren’t too familiar with good Thai?)... they have a HUGE menu (usually a red flag, unless it’s a generic chain like the Cheesecake Factory) and every item we ordered was inedible. We paid full price and left all of the food.  -The seafood platter had no flavor and the sauce was gelatinous. The crab was fake and squishy, the shrimp tasted like nothing. The noodles were the only things with flavor, but unfortunately, they were glued together in a lump. It seemed microwaved.  -The spring rolls were COVERED in another gelatinous sauce and were room temperature and flavorless.  -The Tom Kha Kai soup was just coconut milk, a TON of lemon flavor, and rubbery chicken that tasted greasy and old. No veggies, no onions, just lemon flavored, salty soup.  -The only thing that was edible was the chicken wing plate, and really just because they were fried and there wasn’t much to them.  Why open a restaurant if you’re going to offer food that seems like no care was put into it?? Sorry, guys, but the experience overall was just awful. Our server was nice, but that was it.
Lowkey hidden apot. I love it here. Had a great server, amazing, hot food that came out in a few minutes and AMAZING satay. Definitely recommend this place
Great service!  The quality of food was fine, but just wasnt to my taste.  This may be a place for other people.  I just don't like a very very sweet pad thai

The prices are decent, the food tastes good, the menu has great variety, and the staff are friendly. I've been happy with the portion sizes, quantity of proteins in the food, and the soups are meant to be shared (or for one very hungry customer!). They are located right by the Western Brown line, so very easy to get to, and there is street parking nearby. BYOB, and also has a party room as well. Definitely will be back.
Great Thai food and service. Looking forward to coming back again. Would recommend the Thai sausage dish!
A welcome save from the departed and much loved Opart...the food is just as good and some of the much loved wait staff are still there.
Food tasted OK. Hard to live up ro Opart standards.
The special herb whole chicken is fantastic. Just like what I had in Thailand! This dish is new and was not on the menu at Opart.

Really good food, right off of the brown line so it's good for dinner after work! The "basilly perfect" is a refreshing drink too. I recommend the panang curry and chicken satay. Then again, everything I had here was delicious.

New favorite Thai restaurant! Extensive menu with a lot of options I haven’t heard of before. But with familiars like pad Thai, chicken satay, and Panang curry. 100% recommend you try the Tiger Cry appetizer and the signature Basilly Pearfect lemonade. Friendly staff that would check on us regularly in a homey low key restaurant. Can’t wait to come back
Tasty tasty Thai eats! Great flavors and service.
